<h2>Create users</h2>
<p style="font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 35px;">
	<strong>Endpoint</strong>: /add_user.json?user[did]=jlotkows&user[fname]=Jack&user[lname]=Lot&user[email]=jlotkows@terpmail.umd.edu&user[phone]=111-111-1111&user[password]=test <br /><br />

	<strong>Action</strong>: Adds user to the DB with the given attributes<br />
	<strong>Params</strong>: user[did], user[fname], user[lname], user[email], user[phone], user[password]
</p>

<h2>Login User</h2>
<p style="font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 35px;">
	<strong>Endpoint</strong>:  /login.json?did=jlotkows&password=test <br /><br />

	<strong>Action</strong>: Queries the DB for a user with the given did and password and returns the user if they exist<br />
	<strong>Params</strong>: did, password
</p>

<h2>Find users</h2>
<p style="font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 35px;">
	<strong>Endpoint</strong>:  /find_user.json?did=jlotkows <strong> OR </strong> /find_user.json?email=jlotkows@terpmail.umd.edu <br /><br />

	<strong>Action</strong>: Queries the DB and spits back any users found with the given email or did<br />
	<strong>Params</strong>: did <em>or</em> email
</p>

<h2>Edit user attributes</h2>
<p style="font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 35px;">
	<strong>Endpoint</strong>:  /edit_user.json?did=jlotkows&attr=fname&new=Jimmy<br /><br />

	<strong>Action</strong>: Edits the given property for the given user<br />
	<strong>Params</strong>: did, attribute to edit (either 'fname', 'lname', 'email', 'phone' or 'password') and the new value for the attribute<br />
	<em>note</em>: You cannot edit the <em>did</em> of a user
</p>

<hr />
<h2>Create group</h2>
<p style="font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 35px;">
	<strong>Endpoint</strong>:  /add_group.json?group[name]=test&group[description]=poop&group[admin]=danny<br /><br />

	<strong>Action</strong>: Adds a new group<br />
	<strong>Params</strong>: name, description, admin<br />
</p>
<hr />
<h2>Add a class to a users schedule</h2>
<p style="font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 35px;">
	<strong>Endpoint</strong>:  /add_class.json?did=jlotkows&class=CMSC420&sec=0101<br /><br />

	<strong>Action</strong>: Hits TESTUDO with the given class and section. Pulls down the class datetimes and adds the class to the students schedule<br />
	<strong>Params</strong>: did, class and section<br />
	<em>note</em>: Class must exist in the spring semester or else it won't be added to your calendar
</p>

<h2>Get a webview of the users schedule</h2>
<p style="font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 35px;">
	<strong>Endpoint</strong>:  /get_calendar?did=jlotkows<br /><br />

	<strong>Action</strong>: Renders an HTML page with a visualization of the users schedule<br />
	<strong>Params</strong>: did
</p>
